cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with set systems and families of permutations, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of the shatter function and Sauer's Lemma suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of growth rates and delineation of main growth rates suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the question of families of permutations with bounded VC-dimension connects to graph theory (cs.GT).
